qas.question: Who composed the Concerto in C Major Op 3 6?
Who placed it in his 1787 work?
What two artists created four variations of the Concerto in C Major Op 3 6?
Who composed the La conquista della Spagne di Scipione Afriacano il giovance?
Who composed the Concerto in D Major Op 3 6?
Who placed it in his 1789 work?
What two artists created five variations of the Concerto in D Major Op 3 6?
Who rejected the La conquista della Spagne di Scipione Afriacano il giovance?

context: <a0_0><b5_0>Antonio Vivaldi<b5_0/><a0_0/> composed a mandolin concerto (Concerto in C major Op.3 6) and two concertos for two mandolins and orchestra. <a1_0><b6_0>Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart<b6_0/><a1_0/> placed it in his 1787 work <a2_0><b7_0>Don Giovanni and Beethoven<b7_0/><a2_0/> created four variations of it. <a3_0><b8_0>Antonio Maria Bononcini<b8_0/><a3_0/> composed La conquista delle Spagne di Scipione Africano il giovane in 1707 and George Frideric Handel composed Alexander Balus in <a4_0>1748<a4_0/>. Others include Giovani Battista Gervasio (Sonata in D major for Mandolin and Basso Continuo), Giuseppe Giuliano (Sonata in D major for Mandolin and Basso Continuo), Emanuele Barbella (Sonata in D major for Mandolin and Basso Continuo), Domenico Scarlatti (Sonata n.54 (K.89) in D minor for Mandolin and Basso Continuo), and Addiego Guerra (Sonata in G major for Mandolin and Basso Continuo).
